    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. Validation results demonstrate RH < 1.0 at all five operating points, satisfying the acceptance criterion. Pressure-head and velocity-field validations provide corroborating evidence of model fidelity. The assessment team notes that aleatory variability in the hemolysis index comparison (VR-01) was reviewed qualitatively and judged acceptable, though a structured uncertainty quantification node was not formally linked for that result. On balance, the evidence package supports the decision that the CFD model is credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions under COU1 scope.",
